### Production-level Laravel practices

✅ Form Requests for validation
✅ API Resources for responses
✅ Database Transactions
✅ `lockForUpdate()` to prevent duplicate assignments
✅ Eager loading (`with()`)
✅ Pagination
✅ Separate Delivery tracking timestamps
✅ One Delivery per Order (`unique(order_id)`)
✅ No duplicated `driver_id` data in orders and deliveries
✅ Status updates synchronized with order status

This is very close to what you'd typically see in a well-structured Laravel 11 API used for logistics, food delivery, or e-commerce fulfillment.
